    "ideation": "The Long Drum (Djembe) performance is built on a physical, rhythmic pulse. The eyes act as the 'hands' of the drummer, striking downward on the skin, while the mouth becomes the resonant sound wave inside the drum's body. The animation follows a classic polyrhythmic buildup: starting with a deep, slow bass hit (wide, low-frequency mouth), moving into rapid rim-slaps (sharp, high-frequency eye snaps), and culminating in a rolling tribal crescendo. The color palette uses earthy terracotta and ochre to ground the performance in the physical materials of the drum, with bright yellow highlights representing the sharp 'crack' of a high-tone slap.",
